caption: Genuinely great place. Look no further!

This is easily my favorite spot for a drink in Brighton/Allston. Best mixed drinks, yummy, quality foods, very friendly and nice staff, and comfortable space and atmosphere. Definitely worth stopping by if you’re in the area :)  Edit: Their brunch menu is amazing! The bar seating is open again too. I’m so happy this awesome little spot is crushing it during COVID. Love this place so much and will continue to support! ♥️

I've been here two times now. Once for brunch and once for dinner.  I have to say, the brunch was great though the prices seem a bit high for what they serve. On the other hand, the dinner is a disappointment in a basket. I ordered the roast beef three-way which is stated on there menu as $14. I expected a larger sandwich with generous portion of beef..what I got was a slider size sandwich that cost $14.50 for the "BBQ sandwich" and and extra $1 added on for the "three way" even though it is stated that it is $14 for a Roast Beef Three-Way.  All-and-all it's not a terrible place but for the prices it is a let down and I will not be coming back for dinner any time soon.

Great drink spot that attracts a surprisingly friendly crowd. This bar and grill offers plenty of space, and it usually isn't hard to find a table to unwind with the boys. It's a great, low-stress counterpoint to the louder, younger bars in the area, and the bartenders here really seem to know their way around a cocktail glass. The bar also has a coin-operated pool table and a selection of pinball machines, in case you're looking for something to do. Definitely a new favorite spot in the area.

The environment was comfortable,  casual and quiet to allow easy conversation amongst my family.  I expected the menu to be bar food but it was more upscale,  presented nicely and tasted very good.  I'd highly recommend it.

We want to love Hopewell, we really do! But every time we're let down. We work nearby so on numerous occasions I've tried to plan holiday parties and large group seating here and most of the time management is incredibly unresponsive or difficult to work with. The drinks are pretty good but the food is always just ok, especially for the prices.  The most recent time we went we were a party of 7 and were told we couldn't be seated at a table because we weren't all having full dinner service. So we all huddled around one of the smaller bar areas and bombarded the poor bartender with all of our drink and food orders. At one point I apologized to her saying they wouldn't seat us and she's like they totally could've sat you in the lounge area. The hostess claimed they do it as a courtesy to their waitstaff but it just seemed like all the waitstaff was awkwardly avoiding us as the bartender was unnecessarily swamped between us, the bar, and delivering drinks to tables...what does the waitstaff even do here? Seems like the bartender covers it all. Unfortunately, because of that some of our food and drink orders never arrived to us and we had to reorder them later on.  Certainly doesn't seem like an efficient way to run a restaurant. We were there on a Thursday night and there were maybe 4 tables full. I'm not sure what courtesy the waitstaff got from not serving us, but the bartender sure liked all of our tips.

Ehhhhhh, not a good bar to go to, i guess if you come here for beer and pool night, it's all right, but the food is boujee and the 21 year old college scene during school season is unbearable. If you want to pay a lot for food and see college kids press up against each other😂 this is the place.

We'd rather go to Hawthorne or Eastern Standard for that.  The atmosphere is great, nice for people watching, good music, and friendly staff. The food is also great, different than a typical American restaurant. I loved the chickpea gyro, and my husband really enjoys the steak frites. We've also shared the grilled asparagus, truffle fries, garlic knots, and a few other items on some other trips - all amazing. This is one of our go to places when we have some friends in town.

How does one put such a great menu and ingredients and make it so tasteless. Pizza was soggy. Charcuterie plate lacked flavor, especially the cheese. The steak tasted like nothing. Even the drinks were low flavor. Decor is cool and staff responsive. We liked the shuffle board :)

Pros: Charcuterie board was above average. Steak frites had good steak and nice dipping jus. Earl of Woodford drink was strong and complex. Shuffleboard is immensely fun. Service was ok.  Cons: We sat near the door and it was loud (found out later that the back area is much quieter). Ghost tears drink was disappointingly not spicy. French onion soup was under-salted, under-flavored, was low on crutons, and used a utterly flavorless cheese (maybe the mozzarella they use on the pizza?) instead of gruyere. Fries in the steak frites had super fake truffle aroma. Pizza crust went from crisp to soggy in 10 minutes. Everything was under-salted.  This place has a nice atmosphere and a young crowd. A few tweaks to their food and I'd consider coming back.

During our meal, she didn't ask us one if the food was okay or not. I had to call her again after sitting for a long time to ask for the check and to go boxes. She seemed upset that we wanted the to go boxes. All those people who are wondering how busy the restaurant was that she didn't bother to smile at us once, it was okay busy. It was not bursting with people but it wasn't empty either. When we were leaving, 1 couple was waiting to be seated which is not terribly busy considering a Saturday night.
